":[{"name":"Rodger","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Roger  , in part from the surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705184,"age":6,"year":"1096","julianDay":2121366,"title":"The Crusades","description":"A series of religious wars between Christians and Muslims, known as the Crusades, occurred between 1096 and 1291, and played a large role in European Christian dominance in the Middle East.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/middle-ages/crusades","urlTitle":"History - The Crusades","jurisdictionLevel":3},{"id":1705185,"age":16,"year":"1106","julianDay":2125018,"title":"The Battle of Tichebray","description":"King Henry I defeated and captured his brother, Robert of Normandy, at the Battle of Tinchebray in 1106. Robert remained in captivity until his death in 1134.","jurisdictionLevel":3}],"lifeSummary":"Roger de Raimes was born about 1090 as the son of Roger de Raimes and Lady Roger de Ramis. He married Lady Roger de Ramis after 1100. They were the parents of at least 3 sons and 1 daughter. He died in 1120, in England, at the age of 31, and was buried in St John's Abbey, Colchester, Essex, England."},"et":{"about 1090–1120":"umbes 1090–1120","1090–1120":"1090–1120","1090–Male":"1090–Surnud","–1130":"–1130","1090–Female":"1090–Surnud","1100–1159":"1100–1159","1100–1162":"1100–1162","1115–1140":"1115–1140","1120–1195":"1120–1195","1070–1100":"1070–1100","–1100":"–1100","1090":"1090","about 1090":"umbes 1090","1120":"1120","1130":"1130","1096":"1096","1195":"1195","1140":"1140","1162":"1162","1070":"1070","1106":"1106","1115":"1115","1159":"1159","1100":"1100","after 1100":"pärast 1100","about 1100":"umbes 1100","about 1120":"umbes 1120","Raimes, Normandie, France":"Éraines, Calvados, Normandie, Prantsusmaa","St John's Abbey, Colchester, Essex, England":"St John's Abbey, Colchester, Essex, England","England":"England"},"fi":{"about 1090–1120":"noin 1090–1120","1090–1120":"1090–1120","1090–Male":"1090–Kuollut","–113